==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[stimulatus]]'' past participle of ''[[stimulare]]'' "to goad on" < {{L.}} ''[[stimulus]]'' "[[goad]]".

===Verb===
{{en-verb|stimulat|ing}}

# To [[encourage]] into action.
# To [[arouse]] an organism to functional activity.

====Synonyms====
*(''to encourage into action''): [[encourage]], [[induce]], [[provoke]]
*(''to arouse an organism to functional activity''): [[animate]], [[arouse]], [[energize]], [[energise]], [[excite]], [[perk up]]

====Antonyms====
*(''to arouse an organism to functional activity''): [[de-energize]], [[sedate]], [[stifle]]

